The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 January is 27,153 (3,142.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 January, there were 5,732 new confirmed cases (663.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 December, there were 5,220 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 10% (512 extra cases).
